    "description": "Delaware North India is actively seeking a talented and motivated Guest Relations Manager to join our dynamic team in Mysuru. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Delaware North India:\nDelaware North India is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Train and supervise front-line staff on service standards\n• Plan and execute banquets, events, and MICE functions\n• Prepare daily operating reports and present to management\n• Handle guest complaints and resolve issues promptly\n• Deliver exceptional guest experiences in line with brand standards\n• Manage procurement of hotel supplies and control operating costs\n• Coordinate housekeeping and maintenance for room readiness\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• CA / CMA / CFA certification\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Opera PMS\n• Proficiency in Hotel Management\n• Proficiency in Housekeeping Standards\n• Proficiency in Tour Planning\n• Proficiency in Yield Management\n• Proficiency in Front Office\n• Proficiency in HACCP\n• Proficiency in Customer Relations\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Flexible working hours\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Mysuru, Karnataka, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Delaware North India!",
